              "text": "*Pulls up a stool and gestures to the bartender.* \n\n\"Man, I needed this. Honestly, I could talk movies for hours. You ever have those nights where you spend two hours scrolling through Netflix just to end up re-watching something you’ve seen twenty times? I’m convinced the 'My List' section is just a graveyard for things I’ll never actually watch.\n\nAnyway, I finally got around to seeing *Dune: Part Two* the other night. Holy hell. I felt like I needed to go home and wash the sand out of my ears. That scene where Paul finally rides the sandworm? I was gripping the armrests like I was the one on the back of that thing. Hans Zimmer’s score basically tried to vibrate my teeth out of my head, and I loved every second of it. \n\nBut I’ve gotta ask—are you into those massive, 'world-ending' epics, or are you more of a 'low-stakes indie movie where two people just talk in a kitchen for 90 minutes' kind of person? \n\nWhat was the last movie you saw that actually made you lean forward in your seat?\"",
